Shape.Name: Sheet.2
Shape.Text: The VSA P4000 Solution is an iSCSI LeftHand SAN The E5000 is an Exchange-Centric Server designed for messaging and email/file server use. Business plan is MS Exchange-heavy. Email, database, POS and website processes are needed for business to thrive. VMware is used for business systems and database services on the VSA P4000 solution. This is accompanied by the E5000 Exchange Server solution which is used for pooling email and file data separate of the VSA database and business systems pool. Separating the duty of processing, and dividing pools makes the VSA/E SAN data system both logically and physically easier to upgrade and easier to maintain. Processing is easier on the whole system... such as mine data in the VSA pool while the Exchange pool merrily replicates a backup to the VSA pool, while another server set in the VSA pool prepares to mine the new backup for snap clone… scripted processes … and a many other business data needs… flexible logical processing.

Shape.Name: Sheet.17
Shape.Text: Use HP P4000 Virtual SAN Appliance (VSA) software to turn the D2200sb into an iSCSI SAN for use by all servers in the enclosure and any server on the network. HP VSA software is installed in a virtual machine on a VMware ESX host server adjacent to the D2200sb. HP P4000 VSA turns the D2200sb into a scalable and robust iSCSI SAN, featuring storage clustering for scalability, Network RAID for storage failover, thin provisioning, snapshots, remote replication, and cloning. Expand capacity within the same enclosure or to other Blade System enclosures by adding additional D2200sb Storage Blades and HP VSA licenses. A cost effective bundle of the D2200sb Storage Blade and a HP P4000 VSA license makes purchasing convenient. If storage needs increase, add HP P4300 or P4500 systems externally and manage everything via a single pane of glass.
